msgstr "Progress bar updates per second"

msgctxt "#32086"
msgid "Smooth mode only: how many times per second to refresh the bar (2–120). Default 4 is fine for most displays; raise only if the bar looks choppy on a high-refresh panel (60–120 Hz)—and lower again if playback stutters."
msgstr "Smooth mode only: how many times per second to refresh the bar (2–120). Default 4 is fine for most displays; raise only if the bar looks choppy on a high-refresh panel (60–120 Hz)—and lower again if playback stutters."

msgctxt "#32087"
msgid "Master switch for movies: when off, Skippy does not skip or prompt. While off, Kodi hides the child setting \"Show skip dialog for movies\"."
msgstr "Master switch for movies: when off, Skippy does not skip or prompt. While off, Kodi hides the child setting \"Show skip dialog for movies\"."

msgctxt "#32088"
msgid "Master switch for TV episodes: when off, Skippy does not skip or prompt. While off, Kodi hides the child setting \"Show skip dialog for episodes\"."
msgstr "Master switch for TV episodes: when off, Skippy does not skip or prompt. While off, Kodi hides the child setting \"Show skip dialog for episodes\"."

msgctxt "#32089"
msgid "For segments set to Ask, show the Full or Minimal skip dialog. When off, those segments are not advanced. Requires Enable skip for movies (this row only appears when that is on)."
msgstr "For segments set to Ask, show the Full or Minimal skip dialog. When off, those segments are not advanced. Requires Enable skip for movies (this row only appears when that is on)."

